Just technical update of my old "Big Mek from Dawn of War" model (https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:3350534)

- more polygons for smoother shapes
- updated sculpts of the head, arm, and pants sculpts and some other minor details
- slightly adjusted the pose to make it look better on the table
- re-cut - for 3d printing etc

I want to clarify: this is not a "remake". This is a "remaster" of the old model - to be honest, i didn't even look at the character's pictures from the game while making this remaster. The goal, to use an analogy, was to try not to rework it, but just to "improve textures and fix bugs" — so it wouldn't be such an embarrassment for me anymore and could last for many years to come.

(NON COMMERCIAL of course)

This cephalopod inspired robot is a ghoulish spektor that haunts archeotech ruins.

It is a remix of Akewea's Sci-Fi Sphere Drone (https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:5266420) and Franklima260's Mini Servo Arm (https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/sci-fi-sphere-drone)

The arms are fully posable with ball & socket joints at the shoulder, elbow, and wrist.

Since the attachment point to the base is pretty small, I've included 4 additional versions of the tentacles with a rod cutout for pinning of the following sizes
- 1mm brass rod (1.1mm hole)
- 1.5mm brass rod (1.6mm hole)
- 0.8mm thin paperclip (0.9mm hole)
- 1.15mm thick paperclip (1.25mm hole)

Alloteu (https://cults3d.com/en/users/Alloteu/3d-models) is the original designer of Lawdogs. Evilamericorp (https://cults3d.com/en/users/evilamericorp/3d-models) & Dimkaf (https://cults3d.com/en/users/dimkaf/3d-models) took his models, reposed them, and added additional bits to create alternate models.

I just took Evilamericorp's and Dimkaf's creations, removed the non-Lawdog stuff and collected them together so you could quickly access additional Lawdog models.

Note these guys have no heads! But I've included 3 of Alloteu's Lawdog Heads (with a ball, cylinder, or hole at the bottom) for you to use.

Description :

For a variety of projects I've got on, I needed a set of human heads to add to models I intend to sculpt for 3D printing. I couldn't find any I like, so have made up a collection of heads I've created by scratch sculpting, using Blender Add-ons, etc. None are 'stock' generation. Each has been scratch sculpted, re-sculpted from add-on generated blank faces, modified, re-shaped etc by me to meet the needs of my projects for 28mm - 32mm scale miniatures. 

I really struggled to find any free base heads I could use as a starting block to model onto, so am putting these here as a resource for any other amateur enthusiast designers like me who need a start until our scratch-sculpting talents get to where they need to be!

If you do use them in your own projects, would love to see them.

A modular set of parts for dungeon crawling in the icy void of space.


These parts use OpenLOCK clips to assemble.


You'll find the clip in the 4-Others folder.


https://www.printablescenery.com/product/open-lock/





The pieces do not use the tile system per se.





This set allows you to play games such as Space Hulk, games in the Zone Mortalis environment, Necromunda and other Warhammer 40k SF dystopian universes.





For Space Hulk players, here you'll find everything you need to redo all the missions from V1 and its expansions.


Parts will be added as we go along, enabling you to play the game's 2 expansions.


This being done on my own time, thank you for understanding my pace of adding pieces.





The squares are 33x33 mm, which is a good compromise between the volume of filament required and good playability.


The whole thing can be scaled to suit your aspirations.

An updated version of my previous (now deactivated) file pack for a robotic arm which I made months back. Besides fixing some geometry and STL file issues which were present in the first pack, I also decided to add some additional details to it. The components of the arms are left separate to hopefully avoid non manifold geometry issues as well as allowing anyone to separate the arms for reposing. The claw is also separate from the arm now, allowing some extra freedom in posing. The base and arm also have a slot for a 6mmx3mm circular magnet to keep the two parts together without needing to permanently attach them.

Hope you all enjoy this one and feel free to reach out to me if you encounter any issues with the models. Enjoy

Taking trenches, cities and sectors require troops in the thousands, and waiting for weeks or months on end for the right moment to strike. Other armies decorate these soldiers in honors, having them as elite regiments on their planets. The best of the best.

Using the fantastic model made by FELIXTHECRAZY (along another Ridgerunner proxy that dissapeared time ago and i dont know who made it), i designed this vehicle mostly for my Squat miners, but i think is suitable for Genestealers Cults too.

I cant assure if is a proper Ridgerunner proxy, because i think this model is smaller, but i added all the weapons and accesories listed in GSC army book for the vehicle in case that someone want to use it in that way. Maybe re-escaling it a bit is enough, but i dont how much, i have never seen a real Ridgerunner model before.

The original model is a single piece, meant to be printed in resin, but my experience printing vehicles in resin is not the best, so i prefer print them on PLA. With that in mind, i separated some pieces of the model to make it suitable for FDM printers, specially small parts that will probably break when you try to remove supports, then the best is print them apart and glue them after. Refer the pics to look where each piece goes

Weapons and accesories are small and detailed, and were designed to be printed in resin. You can try to print them in FDM of course, but they will lost a lot of detail, specially with the mining laser.

About the Spotter, i choose a more "technological" option instead a guy with binoculars. It makes more sense i think, and it saved me a lot of work :P

I included the center hull as one piece and in halves. I printed it as one piece, but I think it's easier and faster to print two pieces. Your choice.

I dont discard make some aditional weapons and accesories in the future.

Each weapon comes in three STL variants:
1) weapon by itself

Knife1 and Knife2 have four variants each, two with the blade held normally and two with the blade held ready to stab. You can mirror the weapons with hands on them to create left-handed versions. All total that comes to 68 different options. You can use these files for physical or digital conversions as you see fit. Inspired by the new Votann (return of the squats ;-) i had a reason to finally paint my classic squats in combination with new Votann as one big army.
Being an Epic player with a big Squat army, i also wanted to have a land train for both my squats in 40k and for Necromunda, for that is where squats live.
The Space Dwarf Land Train from taaz was a good basis and from there i made a Land Train 2.0 that i tried to give a post-squat and pre-votann vibe.

I upgraded the train-cars with printable tracks and more details (doors, windows, exhaust pipes, new towbars). Then i added runes to get several different looking train-cars.
Furthermore i made new train-car tops because i wanted a different (lower) height and a more detailed weapon design.

Finally and most importantly i completely redesigned the train engine.
It now also is a playable piece of terrain and has details that fit a model this size in 40k.
The sides are based on the sides from the original from taaz, also as a tribute/thanks, but the rest is redesigned from the ground up.

I got a lot of help from my colleague, LegioXIVguy, in determining the ratio and size. So the overall size is about between New edition Chaos space marines and Primaris marines.

The Underhive Poverty Outreach Team are made up of the members of the Noble Houses. They are equipped with special suits of armor, which they use to stock the many food banks found in the Underhive.

Horace's role in the team, as the bionic tray-holder guy, is to descend the many flights of stairs from Tesco (Spire branch) to the underhive with an entire pallet of donated tinned pineapple chunks in each hand. His powerfists come with a secondary weapon of two rows of firework-launchers which he keeps loaded in hope of a Labour Party victory - when it finally comes after 38,000 years.

Beltanya Zukhal is a legal clerc of the Administratum whose task is to record anything and everything, from dead fluotubes to Astra Militarum empty Autocannon cases and daily casualty on the battlefield. She even records the number of downloads of her STL template.

The first in a series of remixed noise marines to form a complete noise chaos rock band.
This one is to be the vocalist of the band, so I started with a free, general chaos marine, add the retro-like microphone, a also retro-like sonic blaster and the noise backpack. Plus a lot of tiny chaotic decorations such as the severed head, Slaanesh icons, chaos sword etc.
The idea is a band of noise marines clearly in the show-bussines mood, and with a retro look. After all, chaos warriors must wish to have their own idols, true? and the daemonettes? what kind of photo posters do they have in their lair-rooms? that is.

This model is remixed all from free public models:

- For the main body I choose a classic chaos marine from JimsBeanz here in Cluts3D: https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/chaos-space-warrior-with-chain-axe
- The Noise backpack: I choose this free model with retro-vynil detail from evanogainen, Here free in Cults3D: https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/art/sonic-blaster-with-gramophonic-generator
- The Sonic blaster, I liked the hedonistic guitar from LoggyK in Cults3D Here: https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/art/hedonistic-sex-fiend-guitar-wip
- For the retro microphone, I choose this free model from DJaviLozano in Cults3D Here: https://cults3d.com/es/modelo-3d/artilugios/microfono-retro

Donations to the artist welcome!

UPDATE: Found there was some geometry present in heads 1 and 2 for each type that may present problems, so I went through and cleaned it out. If you printed these with resin before, should be wary of little pockets of resin within the mouth. New ones do not have these voids.

There are a lot of orcish heads about this website, but I wanted to make my own. I started by putting together some shapes, mostly toruses and squished spheres, in the general form I wanted compared to available orcish heads, and then sculpted the finer details, until I was happy enough to make multiple expressions from it.

I couldn't settle on a specific nose or teeth type, so I decided to use both in extra combos with all the facial expressions I sculpted, resulting in twenty, 20, different head combinations.

I wanted something that could be used for a number of orcish plans I have coming up, something that could work for more warfam figures that I may produce. Panzerfauste, the fantasy ww2 with british orcs, is a game these could be used for.

Have fun with them and be creative all!

IT'S THE LATE 80's, IN SPAAAAACE!

Everyone has mohawks and piercings!
Industrial Metal head anarchists galore!

Here are a few heavy weapons options for your human sized dudes and dudettes, Inspired by classic Necromunda. I give you low tech solutions to deadly problems.

The BRRT Supression Stubber:
All style and zero substance with this over designed chunk of metal, it'll throw roughly bullet shaped things in a roughly straight line. You'll need steroids top deal with kick up though.

Australian Stubber:
The bullets go in ..... UPSIDE DOWN!?
That's right, make gravity your accomplice when you mow down a MF with this retro gravity fed SOB.

Firehazard:
Loaded with homemade fuel that you can dink in a pinch to get your liver upset, the fire hazard is dangerous to everyone, that's cool right? OSHA are nerds!

BAGL (The Ga-chunk):
The Bow Assisted Grenade Launcher or the BAGL (sometimes called the Ga-chunk!) on account of the sound it makes.
Who says you need fancy gas assisted launching mechanisms? Who had the bright idea to try and launch explosives with smaller explosions?
That guy is dead, because those Ideas are hard to execute.

Why go complicated when you can just update a medieval stonebow with modern polymers and alloys.

Possibly the only "stealth" grenade launcher on the market!

Resin would be Ideal, but I've printed the smaller assault rifles I made on FDM and they barely look any more trash than other necromunda weapons! (0.2 nozzle is necessary)

Rigged version of an ork made by VidovicArts. I used this to create all my ork models so far.

There are a some hidden parts in the file and lots of poses in the pose library of the rig. My workflow with this is as follows:

-Add objects like torsi an weapons to the file an pot them to the right place at the body
-hide all parts you don't need for your boi
-make copy of the rig, the body and all parts you added
-parent all objects to the rig (as objects to specific bones)
-choose a pose from the pose library or create a new one.
-apply all modifiers to the parts
-unparent all objects while keeping their transformation
-boolean unite all objects
-use windows 3D builder to repair any problems in the mesh
-print

Rigged version of an ork made by VidovicArts. I used this to create all my ork models so far.

There are a some hidden parts in the file and lots of poses in the pose library of the rig. My workflow with this is as follows:

-Add objects like torsi an weapons to the file an pot them to the right place at the body
-hide all parts you don't need for your boi
-make copy of the rig, the body and all parts you added
-parent all objects to the rig (as objects to specific bones)
-choose a pose from the pose library or create a new one.
-apply all modifiers to the parts
-unparent all objects while keeping their transformation
-boolean unite all objects
-use windows 3D builder to repair any problems in the mesh
-print

My miniatures are designed to work out of the box with original 28mm Heroquest miniatures.
I always add a version with Heroquest base and one without a base. The weapons and the base are only combined (if possible).
Personally, I now prefer 32mm miniatures. I usually scale them to 112% -115% directly in the slicer.

We at Ill Gotten Games are big fans of the [Vintage RPG Podcast](https://www.stitcher.com/podcast/unwinnable-3/the-vintage-rpg-podcast), and after designing a model for Hambone [the hammer-wielding ranger, Johan](https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:3483772)), I made one for Stu as well. This is Greel, an opportunistic (but deep down, gold-hearted) ex-mercenary company leader/current warlock with a magic ring that can turn him into a tree at the first sight of danger. The model prints without support.

If you haven't checked it out, Hambone and Stu (Horvath, from [unwinnable.com](https://unwinnable.com/)) do a weekly podcast where they discuss tabletop games, and do deep dives into RPGs old and new. This all branches off of Stu's excellent [Instagram feed](https://www.instagram.com/vintagerpg/?hl=en), which is always an insightful read if you're into the history and current state of tabletop roleplaying games. We're proud to be [supporting them on Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/vintagerpg/overview), and you should really check out what they're doing/throw them some bones if you like it as much as we do.

Even within the dogmatic and zealous organisation, that is the Cult of Machines, few can hope to match the fanatism of these monks, who are going so far as to invite the frightening might of the kinetic force into their very own bodies until their skin cracks and their eyes boil in their sockets under the electrical inferno. But the rewards for the faithful far outweigh such petty losses as sight and sense of touch, as they are able to stride into the apocalyptic battlefields of the future almost naked, untouchable by deadly projectiles and shrapnels, for the kinetic force shields their own from the attacks of the unenlightened in a shroud of lightning. And in turn each strike of the arcane weapons of these pilgrims leaves enemies and heretical warmachines alike lying cold and dead, as their bioelectricity is absorbed from their unworthy bodies.

I always felt a certain affection to this model series, since they were some of my very first models. Now, with six good ones, which carry enough bits to remix a squad of twenty if necessary, I feel like a can put them aside for the time being Hope you are as content with them as I am.

Starting today, we're launching "Monster Mondays," a regular feature where we upload a new monster miniature design to our online [storefront](http://www.illgottengames.net/products/?category=Miniatures), with our [Patreon supporters](https://www.patreon.com/illgottengames) getting free access. Each unique character will include RPG rules for our own D6Modular system (currently in beta for our patrons) and rules compatible with 5E Dungeons & Dragons.

First up, we're including Baymara, the Grand Chronicler of High Hivald. Though not technically a monster, she'll be the narrator of our growing monster compendium, and you can consider this "entry zero." (We'll be posting the first official monster entry to Thingiverse later today.) As with all of our upcoming monster designs, Baymara prints without need of support on FDM printers.

For those of you supporting us (or thinking about supporting us) on [Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/illgottengames), our patrons get special access to our store releases as they come out (not to mention license options to sell printed versions of our designs).

Enjoy!

-Character art is by the talented [Benjamin Honeycutt](https://www.artstation.com/benhoneycutt)

Welcome Friends! Cadia has fallen and the guard need manpower more then ever! It is our duty to whip the shattered legion of Cadia and the fresh reinforcements for Armageddon into shape.

Literally.

I have provided four poseable guardsmen and their standard issue lasguns and hellguns. These are print friendly and only need a program such as blender, maya, motionbuilder or 3ds max along with several other options to pose.

Should you take up such a task in the Emperors name be creative and dynamic! Funnel new weapons into the hands of proper Emperor fearing men! But most important of all PLEASE LIST IT AS A REMIX so that generals who come here will be more easily able to find reinforcements and fresh poses.

If the Emperor calls you more to the field of battle be sure to WATCH this page in the top right to be notified every time a new wave arrives.

AVE IMPERATOR!

Toxic Rat – London. Another of Banksy’s rats shows a rat with a barrel of toxic waste spilling across the pavement. Several copies have been seen around LA, but none have been confirmed as being by Banksy. This original one is now barely visible.

This model is part of a series I remixed just to see if it was possible. Here are the rest of them.
